Data analysis

Text

fse

We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and nloptwrap optimizer) to predict fse with group and time_point (formula: fse ~ 1 + group + time_point + group * time_point). The model included login_id as random effect (formula: ~1 | login_id). The models total explanatory power is substantial (conditional R2 = 0.69) and the part related to the fixed effects alone (marginal R2) is of 0.05. The models intercept, corresponding to group = control and time_point = 1st , is at 17.39 (S.E. = 0.66, p < .001, 95% CI [16.09, 18.68]). Within this model:

  • The effect of group [treatment] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.21, S.E. = 0.92, p = 0.816, 95% CI [-2.02, 1.59]; Std. beta = -0.05, 95% CI [-0.51, 0.40])
  • The effect of time point [2nd] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.33, S.E. = 0.79, p = 0.672, 95% CI [-1.88, 1.21]; Std. beta = -0.08, 95% CI [-0.47, 0.30])
  • The interaction effect of time point [2nd] on group [treatment] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 2.98, S.E. = 1.15, p = 0.010, 95% CI [0.73, 5.23]; Std. beta = 0.75, 95% CI [0.18, 1.32])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald normal distribution approximation.
